<subSubSection id="983E032759D70C062CA1276BD5DE02FA" lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="130" pageId="16" pageNumber="129" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="2BF4C671CBF546CECFF1147492373450" pageId="16" pageNumber="129">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ED07753E4981DCCBFA89D289CCBF0C79" lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="130" pageId="16" pageNumber="129">
Members of the 
<taxonomicName id="D262EB146469E52D307EE4C54129632C" authority="Jeannel, 1962" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Antiperyphanes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Antiperyphanes" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<pageBreakToken id="F98B9D6273C12768F7CB4EC9F3AE4F99" pageId="17" pageNumber="130" start="start">Antiperyphanes</pageBreakToken>
</taxonomicName>
Complex are diverse in form (Figs 1-3, 5). There are no recognized derived morphological characteristics of the group, although the clade is moderately well supported by the concatenated DNA sequence data (Fig. 8, Table 3). Within the South American fauna, most species can be recognized by the lack of an N sclerite in the internal sac of the male genitalia (
<bibRefCitation id="0C071CC64921F9FAC7F00BC69A434F8E" author="Toledano, L" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs on Biodiversity" pageId="27" pageNumber="140" pagination="81 - 130" title="Systematic notes on the Bembidiina of the northern Andes with particular reference to the fauna of Ecuador (Coleoptera, Carabidae)." volume="1" year="2008">Toledano 2008</bibRefCitation>
). However, some members of the complex, including some species in subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="0671B1282EEF953E5DC5A6E0F93ED139" authority="Jeannel, 1962" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Nothonepha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nothonepha" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Nothonepha</taxonomicName>
, have a small sclerite that could be homologous to the N sclerite (
<bibRefCitation id="364B6DA454A40757E87EF1E7F872EC7B" author="Toledano, L" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs on Biodiversity" pageId="27" pageNumber="140" pagination="81 - 130" title="Systematic notes on the Bembidiina of the northern Andes with particular reference to the fauna of Ecuador (Coleoptera, Carabidae)." volume="1" year="2008">Toledano 2008</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8379594D0DFD362CC4EA176375BF58D5" pageId="17" pageNumber="130">
The 
<taxonomicName id="5A7689C18A2A9C7DBBD984ED1A14ECDA" authority="Jeannel, 1962" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Antiperyphanes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Antiperyphanes" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Antiperyphanes</taxonomicName>
Complex, as here classified, consists of at least five subgenera: 
<taxonomicName id="CC424C91E7E4AF05F8C86AE9B5E83448" authority="Jeannel, 1962" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Antiperyphanes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Antiperyphanes" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Antiperyphanes</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="B8F5BC7ECB8416B92DB0CE87EA23E9A8" authority="Jeannel, 1962" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Chilioperyphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chilioperyphus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Chilioperyphus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="1A185F8BDC082D0F99146B2122816084" authority="Jeannel, 1962" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Antiperyphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Antiperyphus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Antiperyphus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="C1A4AAE2CC096765E33EDFEA26602D37" authority="Jeannel, 1962" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Notholopha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Notholopha" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Notholopha</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="22BC8989D3AA9E7607B1E6EEC50D974A" authority="Moret &amp; Toledano, 2002" authorityName="Moret &amp; Toledano" authorityYear="2002" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Ecuadion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ecuadion" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Ecuadion</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="F91B42F6C07A5EE2BFD2926C627CA367" authority="Jeannel, 1962" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Nothonepha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nothonepha" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Nothonepha</taxonomicName>
. Each of these subgenera is briefly discussed below, with notes about their composition. Two other poorly known subgenera, 
<taxonomicName id="E4305E67004AAFCC23BECD7F6977C1E5" authority="Jeannel, 1962" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pseudotrepanes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudotrepanes" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pseudotrepanes</taxonomicName>
Jeannel and 
<taxonomicName id="4AF6601E4BF3FC90765C9D1DE8426EDF" authority="Bonniard de Saludo, 1970" authorityName="Bonniard de Saludo" authorityYear="1970" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Notoperyphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Notoperyphus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Notoperyphus</taxonomicName>
Bonniard de Saludo, are likely members of this complex, but specimens will need to be examined to confirm their membership.
</paragraph>
